Changes include adding more details to the target user profile and
updating the value proposition and user stories to match NUScheduler.

JUnit tests are modified as well.

ViewProfilesCommand retains ListCommand's behavior of ignoring everything after the command. For example, `profile -v asdf` is still considered a valid ViewProfilesCommand.

- shift test for parsing of the view profile option flag into
  ProfileCommandParserTest
- rename AddressBookParser to NuSchedulerParser

NUSchedulerParser violates style guidelines due to more than 2
consecutive capital letters. Therefore, the letter "u" is kept as a
small letter.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add telegram username field to Profile
commitResults.messageBody:
Most NUS students use Telegram as their main form of communication with
friends and classmates. It will be beneficial to allow users to store their
connections' telegram usernames as well.

As usernames are not compulsory in telegram itself, the telegram username will be an optional field.
Extra space due to the addition of the telegram field is removed.
